N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 16 ยง 665.11 - Miscellaneous revenues

State Regulations

Miscellaneous revenues are those revenues derived from
the provision of regulated products and services provided under tariff or
contract but not contained elsewhere. They shall also include operating revenue
derived from activities performed incident to the company's tariffed
telecommunications operations which, though nontariffed, are included in the
regulatory process. Notes
